We compared the actions for these different solutions and determined the dominant solution as a function of the two moduli. We confirmed the accuracy of the numerical results by comparing to analytic expectations at special values of the moduli, and in pinching limits at the boundary of the moduli space. There is a line in the moduli space with a $\mathbb Z_3$ symmetry; along this line, we found that the $\mathbb Z_3$ symmetric saddles dominated, and there is a Hawking-Page like phase transition between the connected and disconnected phases. However, along another line in the moduli space with an enhanced $\mathbb Z_2$ symmetry, preserved by the partially connected phase but not the others, the symmetric phase does not always dominate. The full phase diagram is given in figure \ref{fig:phasediagram}. The handlebodies always dominate over the non-handlebody solution. 

